Interface QueryInfo

public interface QueryInfo

A simple structure that shows information about a query.

getKernelID

String getKernelID()
Returns the ID associated to the kernel that created the query.

getID

String getID()
Returns a unique ID for the query. Query IDs are guaranteed to be unique during their lifetime but after a query is completed the ID might be reused for another query in the future.

getQuery

String getQuery()
Returns the SPARQL query string.

Returns the name of the database this query is running on.

String getUser()
Returns the name of the user who is executing this query.

getReasoningType

ReasoningType getReasoningType()

getStartTime

long getStartTime()
Returns the time in milliseconds when the execution of this query started or NO_TIME if the execution did not start. The start time is the exact time when the execution starts on the server which happens after client connection is established, permissions for running the query has been checked, and parsing the query string is completed.

getEndTime

long getEndTime()
Returns the time in milliseconds when the execution of this query ended or NO_TIME if the execution did not end. The end time is the time when the last solution for the query has been computed on the server. The client might receive the results at a time later than this.

getExecutionTime

long getExecutionTime()
Returns the time in milliseconds that has taken for this query to be executed. If the query execution id not start this function will return NO_TIME. If the query is still running this function will return the elapsed since the execution of this query started which is equivalent to System.currentTimeMillis() - getStartTime() and will return a different value over time. If the query execution is finished then the result will be equivalent to getEndTime() - getStartTime() .

getTimeout

long getTimeout()
Return the timeout value in milliseconds for this query or NO_TIME is there is not timeout defined for this query. When the execution time for a query exceeds the timeout value, the query is killed automatically. Timeout value is determined globally by the StardogConfiguration.QUERY_TIMEOUT configuration option and can be overridden for a database using the DatabaseOptions.QUERY_TIMEOUT option.

isStarted

boolean isStarted()
Returns true if the execution of this query started.

isEnded

boolean isEnded()
Returns true if the execution of this query ended.

isRunning

boolean isRunning()
Returns true if the execution of this query started and did not end.
